bad for a guy who has just spent the past two weeks hawking his
12th movie to gaggles of international reporters. He emerges from
the bedroom of a San Francisco hotel suite with a vague Cannes
hangover. There, he'd been practically asking to be drummed into
numbness by giving 20 to 30 interviews a day because his film
