   TRAVEL-HILL-COUNTRY (Fredericksburg, Texas) _ With its rich
German heritage, tourist-friendly attractions, an opportunity to
get close to nature and accommodations that stress both privacy and
comfort, Fredericksburg is typical of the warm hospitality found
throughout the Texas Hill Country. By DAI HUYNH. (Photo available
on NYT database.)
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-LBJ (Johnson City, Texas) _ Driving across the Hill
Country, from Austin to Stonewall and Johnson City, you can sense
the forces that shaped Lyndon Baines Johnson. The 36th U.S.
president has been gone for 26 years, but LBJ left behind large,
lasting imprints for those who want to follow in his footsteps over
some of Texas's prettiest ranch land. By DAI HUYNH. (Photo
available on NYT database.)
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-COMFORT (Comfort, Texas) _ Change doesn't come easy in
Comfort, a town that seems frozen in a time warp. Its quiet charm
provides a stark contrast to neighbor Fredericksburg, but some
long-time residents still insist it's getting too big for their,
er, comfort. By DAI HUYNH. (Photo available on NYT database.)
</P>
