<P>
   MORSE-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ In a building just outside Kansas
City, GuiltAmerica.com continues its research and development of
new ways to use guilt in the marketplace. GuiltAmerica's latest
product for use by nonprofits is called ``Kids 'n' Pledges.'' For
example, children who attend private school knock on doors getting
neighbors to sign pledges to pay a certain amount of money to the
school for each lap they run in a track event. By ROB MORSE.
</P>
