<P>
   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   MIDLIFE-JOURNEY _ DAWSON CITY, Yukon Territory _ They weren't
kidding about this midnight sun business. An hour before midnight,
the sun hangs just above the mountain, flooding my camper, and if
I'm to get any sleep, I may have to climb the mountain with a bat
and beat the sun beneath the horizon. By 1:30 a.m. the sun subsides
just low enough to provide some darkness and with it, blessed
sleep. And the next morning, when the sun blazes out of a cloudless
horizon, warming my face, I bound out of bed and see by my watch
that it is 3:17 a.m. There are no roosters in the Yukon. They are
all in therapy. (EDS: This is Installment 15 in a series of columns
by Ron Wiggins, ``Midlife journey to Mount McKinley.'' If you are
interested in previous columns, please call CoxNet at
404-526-5456.) (Wiggins, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   NEWS-QUESTIONS _ Q&AMP;A on the news, in two takes. (Bessonnette,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) (l, a) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   FOOD
</P>
