   MINOR-COLUMN _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Kalman Gabriel started
this little project that has since landed him an agent, a book and
a 1998 Youth News Writers award. He liked to collect autographs,
but it got to be too expensive. So, he wrote to people, famous
people, and asked them a simple question: ``Dear So and So, I am a
12-year-old boy from Oyster Bay, New York. If you could give me
advice for life, what would it be?'' And for the next three years,
young Kalman kept his mailman on Long Island very, very busy.
(Minor, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
