<P>
   WINE-COLUMN _ DAYTON, Ohio _ What's the hardest thing you've
ever had to do? Wayne Flynn can answer that question. ``The hardest
thing I've ever had to do was to price the first bottle of wine
that I produced,'' said the proprietor of Flynn Winery in Oregon.
The bottle was a 1984 pinot noir. ``I decided to be as close to
under $10 as I could be.'' The wine came out at $9.95. That was
nearly 15 years ago. You know what has happened to wine prices in
the past decade and a half. They've risen faster than a Champagne
cork exits a warm, shaken bottle. Kapow. Through the roof. Flynn
produces two pinot noirs now. So what do you suppose they cost? Um,
$8.99 and $12.99. (The $12.99 wine is the one that used to cost
$9.95, by the way.) And the wines are delicious. (Fisher, Dayton
Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
