<HEADER>
A9726 &Cx1f; tad-z
r d &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FOOD-RECIPESWAP03-COX     06-02 0744
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FOOD-RECIPESWAP03-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Big response is the icing on the cake
 &HT;    By Marcia Langhenry
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ A request from Dorothy Rogers of Decatur (Ga.) almost
a year ago for a poppy seed cake and its ``special icing'' fell
through the cracks here at the Recipe Swap. When it turned up
again, we called Rogers, who said that in the meantime she had
found a recipe but would welcome others.
</P>
<P>
   Within days of publishing her belated request two weeks ago, we
got a variety of responses, ranging from poundcakes to layer cakes
with ``special icings'' from sour cream-based to lemon-sugar syrup
and Seven-Minute Frosting.
</P>
<P>
   We tested and liked these loaves topped with an orange-sugar
syrup. It was e-mailed from M. Ritchie, who got it from a friend
many years ago.
</P>
<P>
   DESSERT
</P>
<P>
   Poppy Seed Cake
</P>
<P>
   Makes 2 loaves, 24 servings
</P>
<P>
   Preparation time: 20 minutes
</P>
<P>
   Cooking time: 1-1 1/2 hours
</P>
<P>
   Standing time: 1 hour
</P>
<P>
   For the cakes:
</P>
<P>
   3 cups all-purpose flour
</P>
<P>
   2 1/3 cups granulated sugar
</P>
<P>
   3 eggs
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 cups milk
</P>
<P>
   1 cup plus 2 tablespoons vegetable oil
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 teaspoons salt
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 teaspoons baking powder
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 tablespoons poppy seeds
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla extract
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 teaspoons almond extract
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 teaspoons butter flavoring
</P>
<P>
   For the glaze:
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup orange juice
</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup granulated sugar
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon almond extract
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon butter flavoring
</P>
<P>
   Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
</P>
<P>
   To make cake: In a large mixing bowl, blend flour, sugar, eggs
and milk. Mix well. Add oil and mix well to incorporate into
batter. Add salt, baking powder, poppy seeds, vanilla, almond
extract and butter flavoring. Mix well. Pour into 2 ungreased
9-by-5-by-3-inch loaf pans. Bake until light brown, 1 to 1 1/2
hours. As cake bakes, make glaze and let it cool.
</P>
<P>
   To make glaze: In a small saucepan, put orange juice, sugar,
vanilla, almond extract and butter flavoring. Mix well. Heat over
medium-high heat until sugar dissolves, about 2 minutes. Let cool.
</P>
<P>
   Remove loaves from oven and cool on racks in pans 10 minutes.
Pour glaze over cakes. Let stand in pans about 1 hour before
serving.
</P>
<P>
   Per serving: 300 calories, 3 grams protein, 15 grams fat
(percent calories from fat, 46), 38 grams carbohydrates, 29
milligrams cholesterol, 206 milligrams sodium, 1 gram fiber.
</P>
<P>
   Recipe requests
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Lillian Strickland of East Point wants to know if anyone has a
recipe for chocolate chess pie like that sold at Rich's bakeries
years ago.
</P>
