 Attn Sports Editors:  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Sports stories from The New York Times News Service for
Thursday, June 3.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-ANDERSON-COLUMN (New York) _ On third game of the series
between the Yanks-Indians, the two best teams in the American
League. By Dave Anderson.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-YANKS-INDIANS (New York) _ Indians-Yankees, 7:30 p.m.; Jaret
Wright, who has become one of baseball's notorious headhunters,
starts for the Indians the day after three batters were hit by
pitches.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-RHODEN-COLUMN (Undated) _ On the Knicks, who now find
themselves tied with the Pacers one game apiece in their Eastern
Conference finals showdown. By William C. Rhoden.
</P>
<P>
