everything about George Washington had long been chewed over. But
wait: What was the connection between the beautiful, whoppingly
productive gardens of Mount Vernon and those famous false teeth?
And by the way, what could our first President eat? ``Not much!''
said Dr. John M. Hyson Jr., director of curatorial affairs at the
Dr. Samuel D. Harris National Museum of Dentistry in Baltimore.
``I'm sure he chewed with great difficulty.'' By Mac Griswold.
