<P>
   PLANE CRASH &QL;
</P>
<P>
   LITTLE ROCK, Ark. _ An American Airlines jetliner, a twin-engine
MD-80 with 145 people aboard, tries to land in a storm at Little
Rock airport, runs off the runway, smashes into a light stanchion,
breaks apart and burns. Initial reports say that nine people died.
Various bylines and various stories in the works. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   F O O D A N D D I N I N G &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-CHAPMAN-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ No one seems to know exactly where it started, but it
has clearly taken on a life of its own. There are rules in some
churches that say there can be no picnics, no socials, no circle
meetings without King Ranch chicken. But as far as anyone can tell,
King Ranch chicken _ or as it is sometimes known _ King Ranch
casserole, doesn't have one single thing to do with the King Ranch.
By ART CHAPMAN. Story will move in ``d'' food and dining category &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-1930S &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Hunger prevails during the Depression, but the food
industry marches on. Another in a series of monthly features on
food during the 20th century. By BEVERLY BUNDY. Story will move in
``d'' food and dining category &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
