   C O M M E N T A R Y &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ And now it begins. With the Texas Legislature
officially adjourned, Gov. George W. Bush can turn his attention to
the business of running for president. Although his candidacy is
not yet official, the possibility that Bush might decide against
making the race is virtually inconceivable. He has come too far to
turn back. The bandwagon has gained too much momentum to suddenly
slam on the brakes. By BILL THOMPSON. Story will move in ``k''
commentary category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BEER-NUT &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Some people just don't have a sense of humor. Take my friend,
Elliott. I wrote about him in a recent column, and now he's
irritated with me. ``Made me sound like a moron,'' he said. I don't
know why _ all I did was call him a Philistine and imply that he's
a sot. ``I was just joshing,'' I replied. ``Too bad you can't write
your own column, ha-ha.'' Well, the swine did it. By BRIAN MELTON
and GUEST. Story will move in ``d'' food and dining category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
