<P>
   LESSONS-INLIFE &QL;
</P>
<P>
   In the summer of 1996, I watched the TCU/Cliburn Piano
Institute's newly instituted ``amateur weekend'' with pure envy. I
was there as part of my job as Star-Telegram classical music
critic. But as often happens to reporters at events they are
supposed to just cover, I came away a changed person. By WAYNE LEE
GAY. Story will move in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL;
