<HEADLINE>
TEST YOUR LITERARY KNOWLEDGE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here's a multiple-choice exercise featuring relatively
unfamiliar works by very well-known authors.
</P>
<P>
   1. The author of ``The Power of Darkness'' is (a) Knut
Hamsun;.MDNM/ (b) Leo Tolstoy; (c) Emile Zola; (d) Stefan Zweig.
</P>
<P>
   2. The author of ``Babette's Feast'' is (a) Isak Dinesen; (b)
Selma Lagerlof; (c) Halldor Laxness; (d) Sigrid Undset.
</P>
<P>
   3. The author of ``Hard Times'' is (a) Charles Dickens; (b)
Gunter Grass; (c) Maurice Maeterlinck; (d) John Steinbeck.
</P>
<P>
   4. The author of ``White Bird Flying'' is (a) Louisa May Alcott;
(b) Bess Streeter Aldrich; (c) Alice Hegan Rice; (d) Gene
Stratton-Porter.
</P>
<P>
   5. The author of ``Our Mr. Wrenn'' is (a) Prentice Upton; (b)
Upton Sinclair; (c) Sinclair Lewis; (d) Louis Bromfield.
</P>
<P>
   6. The author of ``Alexander's Bridge'' is (a) Willa Cather; (b)
Ellen Glasgow; (c) Katherine Anne Porter; (d) Edith Wharton.
</P>
<P>
   7. The author of ``A World I Never Made'' is (a) James T.
Farrell; (b) William Faulkner; (c) F. Scott Fitzgerald; (d) Ernest
Hemingway.
</P>
<P>
   8. The author of ``The Ides of March'' is (a) John Dos Passos;
(b) George Santayana; (c) Thornton Wilder; (d) Ben Ames Williams.
</P>
<P>
   9. The author of ``The Deer Park'' is (a) Saul Bellow; (b)
Norman Mailer; (c) Bernard Malamud; (d) Herman.MDNM/ Wouk.
</P>
<P>
   10. The author of ``Lucy Crown'' is (a) Truman Capote; (b) J.D.
Salinger; (c) Irwin Shaw; (d) Bill Bryson.
</P>
<P>
   11. The author of ``When She Was Good'' is (a) Joan Didion; (b)
John Irving; (c) Joyce Carol Oates; (d) Philip Roth.
</P>
<P>
   12. The author of ``Harvey'' is (a) Mary Coyle Chase; (b) Mary
Ellen Chase; (c) Mary Ann Evans; (d) Mary Ellen Peipert.
.MDBO/.MDNM/Quiz answers:.MDBO/.MDNM/ 1-b; 2-a; 3-a; 4-b; 5-c; 6-a;
7-a; 8-c; 9-b; 10-c; 11-d; 12-a.MDBO/.MDNM/ &QL;
</P>
