<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-KIDS:VIDEO-GAME:SUPER-SMASH-BROS-CLASSACTS-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
VIDEO GAME REVIEW: SUPER SMASH BROS. 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 By NATHAN SCHNURMAN 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   SUPER SMASH BROS. (Nintendo for Nintendo 64, all ages)
</P>
<P>
   Description: Super Smash Bros. is a fun, action-packed game in
which your favorite Nintendo characters duke it out with one
another.
</P>
<P>
   High points: The creativity and the originality of the music,
levels and moves are good role models for Nintendo 64 game-makers.
Instead of one hero, there are 12. Eight are original Nintendo
characters: Mario, Donkey Kong, Yoshi, Kerby, Fox, Link, Samus and
Pikachu. The four other characters are bonus round prizes, such as
Jiggly Puff from Pokemon.
</P>
<P>
   Low points: After a while, you get sick of doing the same old
thing over, over and over! Even though the moves of the eight
original characters are included in the instructions, when in
action, they're difficult to remember.
</P>
<P>
   Rating: For an overall rating, I give this a B. It was really
fun at first, but after a while, it got boring.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; -0- &QL; 
 &UR; Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram &QL; 
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &QL;
</P>
