<HEADLINE>
MOVIE REVIEW: ``STAR WARS EPISODE I _ PHANTOM MENACE'' 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 Includes one color slide of a scene from ``Star Wars Episode I _
Phantom Menace.''
 By AARON PLASKONOS 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Title: ``Star Wars: Episode I _ The Phantom Menace.''
</P>
<P>
   Starring: Jake Lloyd, Ewan McGregor, Samuel L. Jackson, Liam
Neeson, Natalie Portman.
</P>
<P>
   Why go see it?: This is probably the most anticipated movie
ever. Sadly though, the movie would only be ``OK'' except for the
fact that it is a ``Star Wars'' movie. The plot wasn't all that
great, but the special effects were phenomenal. The light saber
battles were awesome and I seriously recommend you see this movie.
</P>
<P>
   Reason for rating: PG for violence.
</P>
<P>
   Reviewer's 1 - 10 score: 8.
</P>
<P>
   STAR FACT
</P>
<P>
   On opening day, the film grossed $28.5 million at 2,970 U.S.
theaters, a single-day record. That knocked to second place the
$26.1 million set by ``The Lost World: Jurassic Park'' in 1997.
</P>
