   BC-KIDSAFE-COMPUTERS-LADN (Los Angeles) _ Worried more than ever
in the wake of various school shootings about what your children
are doing on the computer? Two Intel senior managers have recently
come out with a book that may provide some useful suggestions,
``The PC Dads Guide to Becoming a Computer-Smart Parent'' (DTP
Trade Paperbacks; $13.95) By David Bloom.
</P>
