<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Thursday, June 3, and thereafter. The stories will carry the
``f'' financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For
questions about stories, contact David Brady at the Daily News,
(818) 713-3470.
</P>
<P>
   LITTON-EARNINGS (Los Angeles) _ Earnings are due Thursday for
Litton Industries, which is trying to buy Avondale Industries and
Newport News Shipbuilding. Litton, the big defense contractor and
commercial ship builder, is expected to report about a 12 percent
gain in its third quarter earnings. By Gregory J. Wilcox.
</P>
<P>
   LOGO-LEADER (Los Angeles) _ Lumeni Productions, one of
Hollywood's specialists in generating movie logos and titles for
the past two decades, has aggressively expanded its capabilities by
bringing on Disney's former visual effects supervisor. By Dave
McNary.
</P>
<P>
   CKE-EARNINGS (Los Angeles) _ Shares of CKE, parent of fast-food
chains Carl's Jr. and Hardees, melt down by 25 percent on a
less-than-beefy earnings outlook. By Ben Sullivan.
</P>
<P>
   TODD-SALE (Los Angeles) _ Post-production specialist Todd-AO
Corp., which has generated little enthusiasm on Wall Street over
the past year, has hired investment bankers to explore putting the
company up for sale. By Dave McNary.
</P>
