Linux, has just released a new version that comes with a GUI,
WordPerfect and other apps, and an installer that's supposed to
eliminate most of the hassles that used to be involved in setting
it up. Red Hat and others are moving in the same direction. Is this
just for geeks at home, or could it eventually reach the masses? By
