   _ MSNBC's  &UR; Jeannette Walls  &LR; says that CBS is trying to lure
 &UR; Oprah Winfrey &LR;  into doing its morning show with  &UR; Bryant Gumbel &LR; .
Winfrey doesn't need a co-host, the fame or the money, but the
thinking is that the morning show would be a challenge for her.
</P>
<P>
   _ New York Mayor  &UR; Rudy Giuliani &LR;  said at a fund-raiser this week
that he was going to Arkansas. ``I'm going to say, `I've never
lived in Arkansas, I've never worked in Arkansas, I've never been
to Arkansas, but I love Arkansas. In fact, I love it so much I'm
going to be running for the Senate. And do you know how I'm going
to prepare for it? I'm going to come here and take a vacation, in
Arkansas.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Don Thompson  &LR; notes that &UR; Charles Pierce &LR; , who died in Los
Angeles this week, never allowed himself to be called a female
impersonator. He always said he was a ``male comedienne.''
</P>
