<HEADLINE>
AS FREUD SAID, IT'S HOW YOU HIT THE BALL
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``l'' lifestyle file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; Steve Turner &LR; , who is a student of Kabbalah and  &UR; Sigmund Freud &LR; 
and is Manhattan's $130-an-hour guru of tennis lessons, told the
New York Observer that most people he teaches want to work on their
serves. ``The funny thing is, every woman that I've ever taught
always wants a stronger serve. They want more of a phallus, more of
a phallic push in a phallic sense, not only genital, but phallus
meaning the symbol of a phallus in the society: power! Women want
more power and so the serve presents that.''
</P>
<P>
   What men want, said Turner, is to win. The server serves ``into
a service box. The service box is like the young female. ... So
your serve, which is the hardest shot, is a big, linear phallic
serve into the female.''
</P>
<P>
   The net, he says, symbolizes the mother. The male player has
``to overcome the mother to get into the desired wife or female.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ MSNBC's  &UR; Jeannette Walls  &LR; says that CBS is trying to lure
 &UR; Oprah Winfrey &LR;  into doing its morning show with  &UR; Bryant Gumbel &LR; .
Winfrey doesn't need a co-host, the fame or the money, but the
thinking is that the morning show would be a challenge for her.
</P>
<P>
   _ New York Mayor  &UR; Rudy Giuliani &LR;  said at a fund-raiser this week
that he was going to Arkansas. ``I'm going to say, `I've never
lived in Arkansas, I've never worked in Arkansas, I've never been
to Arkansas, but I love Arkansas. In fact, I love it so much I'm
going to be running for the Senate. And do you know how I'm going
to prepare for it? I'm going to come here and take a vacation, in
Arkansas.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Don Thompson  &LR; notes that &UR; Charles Pierce &LR; , who died in Los
Angeles this week, never allowed himself to be called a female
impersonator. He always said he was a ``male comedienne.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Jason Alexander &LR;  (not the actor) says a classified-ad taker
became cool on the phone when he dictated his description of
himself as an `` &UR; Ayn Rand &LR;  admirer missing heroine.'' He found out
why when the ad said he was ``missing heroin.''
</P>
