   &UR; LADIES, START YOUR ENGINES &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ They all look alike: After working late Tuesday night, a
Hambrecht &AMP; Quist broker found her Jaguar in the garage, turned the
keys in the ignition and drove away. A mile  &LR; down the road, she
realized she was driving the wrong Jag. A major U-ey ensued.
</P>
<P>
   _ In a story about ``What's Sexy Now,'' Mode magazine, which
purports to be for the modern woman, suggests what she need
remember when she finds something amusing or pleasant: ``When
smiling, lift the corners of your lips but don't flash your teeth.
Quiet amusement gives your face an air of tranquil mystery.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Researchers at the University of Michigan ``were asked to
complete a math test while alone in a room and wearing either a
sweater or a bathing suit,'' reports Self magazine. ``All of the
women scored lower than the men, and the women in swimsuits did
worse than the women in clothes.'' The finding: Women's
self-consciousness ``interfered with their performance.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Ladies' Home Journal, apparently going upscale, suggests
cleaning your diamonds by dipping them in vodka.
</P>
<P>
   _ It was  &UR; Dale Evans &LR;  who wrote the words and music to ``Happy
Trails,'' says  &UR; Skye Atman &LR; .
