   (NYT22) BLOOMFIELD HILLS, Mich. -- June 2, 1999 --
CRANBROOK-RENOVATION-1, 6-2 -- A Cranbrook School dining chair by
Eero Saarinen. Cranbrook offers a vibrant reminder that modernism
is not exclusively the realm of sharp right angles and cold, flat
surfaces, of glass and steel. In other words, that there is a place
for the tactile, the colorful and the irregular, for the handiwork
and sensuousness of rough masonry and glazed tile, even - dare one
say it? - for the picturesque. (David Dunlap/New York Times Photo)
