<P>
   (NYT13) UNDATED -- June 2, 1999 -- HOME-IMPROVEMENT-B&AMP;W, 6-2 --
During the spring and summer months, homeowners keep their windows
open to allow fresh air to circulate through the house. It is
important to make sure the screens are clean before opening the
windows; otherwise, dirt on the screens will blow into the house.
Screens with extensive damage should be replaced. If the frame is
solid and in good shape, you only need a roll of new screening
material. (Edward R. Lipinski/New York Times Illustration) LITE
</P>
