<P>
   (NYT9) JOHNSON CITY -- June 2, 1999 -- -TRAVEL-LBJ-HNS, 6-2 --
The grave of President Lyndon B. Johnson in the Johnson Family
Cemetery, situated in the Lyndon B. Johnson National Historical
Park which is among many Texas Hill Country sites associated with
the 36th U.S. president. LBJ's career thrived on Capitol Hill, but
the 36th president of the United States often returned to his ranch
near Johnson City and Stonewall.(Joseph Deering/Houston Chronicle)
