<P>
   (NYT4) SEATTLE -- June 2, 1999 -- CIR-STEPHENSON, 6-2 -- Neal
Stephenson a during a recent interview. Stephenson, who is known
for his best- selling science fiction novels ``Snow Crash'' and
``The Diamond Age,'' has a new novel, ``Cryptonomicon,'' that has
reached No.15 on the New York Times best-seller list despite being
918 pages long and having cryptography as its central subject.
(Robert Sorbo/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT3) LOS ANGELES -- June 2, 1999 -- CIR-LATIN-INTERNET, 6-2 --
Luis Hernandez, 18, an 11th grader at Hollywood High School, using
his school's library computer to keep in touch with friends in
Mexico and check for releases of his favorite music. As they rush
to sign up Spanish-language consumers, Internet giants in the U.S.
face stiff competition from both Latin American media companies and
existing United States-based Spanish-language portals. (Chris
Pizzello/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) NEW YORK -- June 2, 1999 -- CIR-BABY-SOFTWARE, 6-2 --
Aliza Borish, 6, plays on her computer as her siblings, Isabel, 4,
and Harley, 8, watch television in their Manhattan apartment. Not
so long ago, parents were encouraged to hang black-and-white
mobiles above cribs to stimulate newborns and to press headphones
to their pregnant bellies to expose the unborn to Mozart. These
days, many parents view the computer as a symbol of a
technology-laden tomorrow and want even the tiniest citizens of the
future to be prepared. (Craig Wallace Dale/New York Times Photo)
LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) DORCHESTER, Mass. -- June 2, 1999 -- MA-WETLANDS-BOS, 6-2
-- Rich Kleiman, working for the Neponset River Watershed
restoration project, checks out the height of phragmites, or common
reeds, that has taken over parts of the Neponset salt marsh, the
oldest protected marsh in the country. After centuries of watching
much of nature's most valuable real estate disappear beneath
cities, farms and other human constructions, Massachusetts is
taking a national lead in fighting back. (Pam Berry/Boston Globe
Photo)
</P>
