<P>
   ATTENTION EDITORS: The following photos are part of tonight's
New York Times Photo Package, moving 06/02/99. Photo clients will
automatically receive these photos via AP's PhotoExpress or may
download them from either the Wieck Photo Database in Dallas at
972-392-0888 or from NYTPhotos on Newscom at 305-448-8411.
Non-clients can make individual purchases by calling (888) 603-1036
or 212-556-4204.
</P>
<P>
   CORRECTION:
</P>
<P>
   The captions for photos NYT16 and NYT17, which moved on Tuesday,
left an incorrect impression about the location of a fire in
Florida. The smoke billowing on the horizon, over a higway in the
foreground, was from a different fire near Venice, in west-central
Florida on the Gulf of Mexico, not in the Okefenokee Swamp, which
is partly in northern Florida. The photos were slugged:
FL-WILDFIRES-FLOATER
</P>
