<SLUG> BC-RAC-BELMONT-NOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FINALLY, CHARISMATIC FAVORED
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By KEVIN MODESTI  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ELMONT, N.Y. _ Six months and 11 starts after he was last
favored to win a race, Charismatic is the 2-1 low number on the
Belmont Stakes morning line announced Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   All it took was victories in the Kentucky Derby (at 31-1) and
Preakness (at 8-1) to turn him into the people's choice.
</P>
<P>
   Presumably.
</P>
<P>
   ``At least we are until they start betting,'' trainer D. Wayne
Lukas said, apparently not convinced the fans are convinced.
</P>
<P>
   Menifee, second in the Derby and Preakness, is the 7-2 second
choice in the 12-horse field, and Silverbulletday, the filly with
the eight-race winning streak, is third at 4-1.
</P>
<P>
   Charismatic drew the comfortable post 4, next to Silverbulletday
in post 3. Menifee got post 10 in the blind draw.
</P>
<P>
   The 11 opponents for Charismatic would be the most in a Belmont
with a Triple Crown on the line since 12 ran against Canonero
(beaten by Pass Catcher) in 1971. No Triple Crown winner has beaten
more than seven horses in the Belmont.
</P>
<P>
   ``Anybody that has a Belmont horse and is ready to run, they
should get in there, so when we look back Sunday morning, whether
(the winner is) us or somebody else, we can say this was the best
horse,'' Lukas said.
</P>
<P>
   That's a shot at Bob Baffert, who didn't enter Silverbulletday
in the Derby or Preakness but also didn't discourage speculation
she'd have won.
</P>
<P>
   Said Bob Lewis, who, with his wife Beverly, owns Charismatic:
``Bring 'em on, whether they're fillies or colts. Bring 'em all
on.''
</P>
<P>
   Fasten your seatbelts: Lukas said the Wednesday-morning flight
that brought Charismatic _ as well as Silverbulletday, Pineaff and
Prime Directive _ from Louisville was smooth despite the lightning
storms that delayed it for more than an hour.
</P>
<P>
   ``All the horses traveled well,'' Lukas said, adding
facetiously, ``except for Silverbulletday; she was reluctant to get
on.''
</P>
<P>
   Baffert's decision to enter the filly was a hot topic.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think she deserves a chance,'' Menifee trainer Elliott
Walden said of Silverbulletday. ``I don't know if I'd do it in the
Belmont...''
</P>
<P>
   Nice place to visit: Walden brought Kentucky-based Menifee to
New York early enough to give him a 5-furlong workout over the
Belmont track Tuesday. The trainer enjoys the lush stable area.
</P>
<P>
   ``They're big barns, big stalls, a beautiful backside,'' Walden
said. ``If I wasn't concerned about my children being mugged, I'd
probably move here and race here all the time.''
</P>
<P>
   Best bet? Chris Antley, the Charismatic jockey who publishes his
own stock-market newsletter, offered his latest ``buy'' tips:
Yahoo, America Online and CMGI, also an Internet company.
</P>
<P>
   ``My Triple Crown for the week,'' Antley said.
</P>
<P>
   For early risers: Lukas said Charismatic will go out for a
gallop at 5:30 (EDT) this morning.
</P>
<P>
   Charismatic completed his serious workouts Tuesday by going 5
furlongs in 1:00 2/5 at Churchill Downs.
</P>
<P>
   How about 999? The morning-line maker was lenient toward
Teletable, making him (begin ital)only(end ital) 99-1.
</P>
<P>
   The son of 1993 Belmont winner Colonial Affair has never raced
above the maiden level, winning once in four starts, not at all
since Feb. 15. Teletable is the latest longshot to be entered in a
Triple Crown race by owner Robert Perez and Alfredo Callejas.
</P>
<P>
   Sign here, please: Visa renewed _ through 2005 _ its sponsorship
of the $5 million bonus for winning the Triple Crown.
</P>
<P>
   Looking ahead: Walden said 1998 Belmont winner Victory Gallop is
aiming for the Aug. 29 Pacific Classic at Del Mar.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
